GMC Duramax 2001-2004.5 LB7 6.6L High Performance Injector 

Where High Performance meets High Standards

This injector can support up to 750 horsepower, and is a 25% horsepower gain at stock (in stage 1) or approximately a 60 horsepower increase! 

Note: High performance parts are meant for off-road use only.

  • TDM tests and calibrates all injectors on OE test bench and tests through the full operating pressure range following the OEM fuel maps.
  • They have developed a proprietary formulation or the internal adjustments and specifications that allows them to optimize performance not only at full load but throughout the fuel map.

  • Torque Diesel Motorsports has developed a superior performance injector based on the demands of today's Diesel performance customer.  Truly a blend of engineering and craftsmanship, TDM injectors provide the performance you want, the quality you expect, and the reliability you need.

 

About Torque Diesel Motorsports

Torque Diesel Motorsports goes through incredible lengths to produce the best performance injectors available in the market today. At Torque Diesel Motorsports our team of highly trained technicians has produced in excess of 50,000 injectors and builds each performance injector by hand. We start by completely disassembling each injector, the injector body then goes through a multi-stage ultrasonic cleaning process and all internal wear parts are discarded. Next, each body undergoes a strict internal inspection before being marked with a laser annealed serial and part number.

Torque Diesel Motorsports currently operates the largest OE authorized clean room in North America where all of our injectors are built under the supervision of our in house engineering team. We have developed a proprietary formulation for the internal adjustments and specifications that allows us to optimize performance not only at full load but throughout the fuel map. Using strict guidelines set forth by the OE manufacturer, we replace every solenoid, valve set, spring, O-ring, control ball, ball sleeve, thrust piece, and shims with new genuine Bosch parts. In order to ensure long lasting quality and reliability, Torque Diesel Motorsports exclusively uses 100% new OE nozzles featuring the latest DGV (double guided valve) design.

Torque Diesel Motorsports tests and calibrates all of our injectors exclusively on a OE – EPS 815 Common Rail test stand. Each injector is tested through the full operating pressure range following the fuel maps provided by the original equipment manufacturer to ensure reliable performance. Our testing also includes the proprietary shot to shot measurement at a minimum of five different test points. Shot to shot testing measures the output of each injection event during the testing sequence to ensure superior performance and repeatability. the OE team annually re-calibrates and re-certifies each of our three common rail test stands to ensure both the accuracy and consistency of our results. It is our combination of internal adjustments, exclusive use of new original equipment parts, and advanced manufacturing processes that allows us to provide an unmatched level of quality and performance.

Installation Guide Cummins 6.7 Dodge 2007-2012

  1. Thoroughly clean injector cylinder head bore. Blow out bore hole with compressed air.
  2. Lubricate the injector O-ring and cylinder head bore with clean engine oil.
  3. Place injector into bore with mounting flange positioned toward the rocker levers and the fuel inlet hole facing the intake side of the engine. Push down on flange to engage O-ring and seat injector.
  4. Tip: Use the plastic solenoid cap to prevent breaking the solenoid terminals when inserting the injector into the bore
  5. Install mounting flange bolts.Make sure flange is perpendicular to injector body.  Tighten to 5 Nm (44 in. lbs.)
  6. Relieve flange bolt torque, but leave both bolts threaded in place.  It is HIGHLY RECOMMENDED to replace the high pressure fuel connector with each new injector. Evidence of fuel connector contamination may not be visible.
  7. Install high-pressure connector and retaining nut.  Tighten to 15 Nm (11 ft, lbs.)
  8. Tighten the injector flange bolts making sure to tighten the flange bolts evenly. Check that the gap between the flange and the injector is equally spaced around the injector body.  Tighten finger-tight and alternate between bolts turning 90 degrees per turn until reaching: 10 Nm (89 in. lbs.)
  9. Do final tightening of high-pressure fuel connector retaining nut. Tighten to 50 Nm (37 ft. lbs.)
  10. Connect and injector solenoid wires. Be sure the solenoid wires can NOT make contact with the rocker levers when installed.  Tighten to 1.25 Nm (11 in. lbs.)

entry.title: Fuel Additive Sampler Pack
entry.summary:
Vendor: Stanadyne
Type: Additive
Price: 60.00

New to Diesel Fuel Additives and not sure which one to buy? Or just want to try out the industry-leading offerings? Here's your chance! Diesel Parts Canada is happy to have a Fuel Additive Sample Pack available, where you get one of each of the following products:

One 16 oz bottle of Alliant Power ULTRAGUARD Diesel Fuel Treatment
All-season, multi-functional fuel treatment that provides complete fuel system and injector protection for all diesel engines.

One 16 oz bottle of Alliant Power LUBRIGUARD Diesel Fuel Treatement
Highly concentrated lubricating fuel treatment with cetane improver that provides superior fuel system protection for all diesel engines.

One 16 oz bottle of Alliant Power WINTERGUARD Diesel Fuel Treatment
﻿Cold weather fuel treatment designed to prevent common diesel fuel issues relating to extreme cold temperatures.

One 8 oz bottle of Stanadyne Performance Formula All Season Diesel Fuel Additive
The premium all-season, multi-function diesel fuel additive, designed to tackle virtually any diesel fuel related problem.

One 8 oz bottle of Stanadyne Performance Formula Warm Weather Blend Diesel Fuel Additive
Formulated to provide the same benefits as Performance. Formula All Season Protection (Blue Label) except without cold weather protection. Performance Formula Warm Weather Blend is recommended when ambient temperatures are above 40°F (4° C).

One 8 oz bottle of Stanadyne Performance Formula Injector Cleaner Diesel Fuel Additive
Stanadyne Performance Formula Injector Cleaner is formulated to prevent and eliminate Internal Diesel Injector Deposits (IDID) commonly found in Common Rail and other type of Injectors. These deposits affect injector performance, which results in various engine related issues.

One 8 oz bottle of Stanadyne Lubricity Formula Diesel Fuel Additive
Extra strength lubricity formula to protect fuel systems against the effect of untreated diesel fuel.

Where High Performance meets High Standards

  • TDM tests and calibrates all injectors on OE test bench and tests through the full operating pressure range following the OEM fuel maps.

  • Torque Diesel Motorsports has developed a superior performance injector based on the demands of today's Diesel performance customer.  Truly a blend of engineering and craftsmanship, TDM injectors provide the performance you want, the quality you expect, and the reliability you need.

 

About Torque Diesel Motorsports

Torque Diesel Motorsports goes through incredible lengths to produce the best performance injectors available in the market today. At Torque Diesel Motorsports our team of highly trained technicians has produced in excess of 50,000 injectors and builds each performance injector by hand. We start by completely disassembling each injector, the injector body then goes through a multi-stage ultrasonic cleaning process and all internal wear parts are discarded. Next, each body undergoes a strict internal inspection before being marked with a laser annealed serial and part number.

Torque Diesel Motorsports currently operates the largest OE authorized clean room in North America where all of our injectors are built under the supervision of our in house engineering team. We have developed a proprietary formulation for the internal adjustments and specifications that allows us to optimize performance not only at full load but throughout the fuel map. Using strict guidelines set forth by the OE manufacturer, we replace every solenoid, valve set, spring, O-ring, control ball, ball sleeve, thrust piece, and shims with new genuine Bosch parts. In order to ensure long lasting quality and reliability, Torque Diesel Motorsports exclusively uses 100% new OE nozzles featuring the latest DGV (double guided valve) design.

Torque Diesel Motorsports tests and calibrates all of our injectors exclusively on a OE – EPS 815 Common Rail test stand. Each injector is tested through the full operating pressure range following the fuel maps provided by the original equipment manufacturer to ensure reliable performance. Our testing also includes the proprietary shot to shot measurement at a minimum of five different test points. Shot to shot testing measures the output of each injection event during the testing sequence to ensure superior performance and repeatability. the OE team annually re-calibrates and re-certifies each of our three common rail test stands to ensure both the accuracy and consistency of our results. It is our combination of internal adjustments, exclusive use of new original equipment parts, and advanced manufacturing processes that allows us to provide an unmatched level of quality and performance.

﻿

Installation Guide Cummins 6.7 Dodge 2007-2012

  1. Thoroughly clean injector cylinder head bore. Blow out bore hole with compressed air.
  2. Lubricate the injector O-ring and cylinder head bore with clean engine oil.
  3. Place injector into bore with mounting flange positioned toward the rocker levers and the fuel inlet hole facing the intake side of the engine. Push down on flange to engage O-ring and seat injector.
  4. Tip: Use the plastic solenoid cap to prevent breaking the solenoid terminals when inserting the injector into the bore
  5. Install mounting flange bolts.Make sure flange is perpendicular to injector body.  Tighten to 5 Nm (44 in. lbs.)
  6. Relieve flange bolt torque, but leave both bolts threaded in place.  It is HIGHLY RECOMMENDED to replace the high pressure fuel connector with each new injector. Evidence of fuel connector contamination may not be visible.
  7. Install high-pressure connector and retaining nut.  Tighten to 15 Nm (11 ft, lbs.)
  8. Tighten the injector flange bolts making sure to tighten the flange bolts evenly. Check that the gap between the flange and the injector is equally spaced around the injector body.  Tighten finger-tight and alternate between bolts turning 90 degrees per turn until reaching: 10 Nm (89 in. lbs.)
  9. Do final tightening of high-pressure fuel connector retaining nut. Tighten to 50 Nm (37 ft. lbs.)
  10. Connect and injector solenoid wires. Be sure the solenoid wires can NOT make contact with the rocker levers when installed.  Tighten to 1.25 Nm (11 in. lbs.)
